@* 
Component: StartupGate
Purpose:
- Acts as a startup guard that runs once on first render and routes the user to the correct entry page:
  - If this is the first run (no owner profile exists): navigate to "/register-owner".
  - Otherwise: navigate to "/login".

How it works:
- Uses OnAfterRenderAsync(firstRender: true) so navigation occurs after the first UI render (safe for NavigationManager redirect).
- Calls IOwnerRegistrationService.CheckFirstRunAsync() to determine first-run state.
- Uses a local _checked flag to ensure the navigation logic runs only once per render cycle and avoids duplicate redirects.

Where to place:
- Include once in Routes.razor inside the <Found> block so it evaluates on application startup or first navigation:
  <Router ...>
    <Found Context="routeData">
      <StartupGate />
      <RouteView RouteData="routeData" />
    </Found>
    ...
  </Router>

Dependencies:
- IOwnerRegistrationService: provides the first-run check.
- NavigationManager: performs the redirect.

Blazor hosting notes:
- Blazor Server: interactive by default; no extra render mode needed.
- Blazor Web App (.NET 8): ensure this component (or its parent) uses an interactive render mode (e.g., InteractiveServer) so eventing and navigation occur on the server.

Extensibility ideas (optional):
- Add error handling (try/catch) and fallback route if the service call fails.
- Add a small loading indicator while the check is in progress.
- Add a parameter to opt-out of automatic navigation for testing.

Testing guidance:
- Mock IOwnerRegistrationService.CheckFirstRunAsync() to return true/false and assert that NavigationManager.NavigateTo is called with the expected route.
*@
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization
@inject BootManager.Application.OwnerRegistration.Services.IOwnerRegistrationService RegistrationService
@inject NavigationManager Nav

@code {
    [CascadingParameter] private Task<AuthenticationState>? AuthenticationStateTask { get; set; }
    private bool _checked;

    protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
    {
        if (!firstRender || _checked) return;

        var relative = Nav.ToBaseRelativePath(Nav.Uri).Trim('/');
        var firstRun = await RegistrationService.CheckFirstRunAsync();

        // 1) First run: always go to register page
        if (firstRun.IsFirstRun)
        {
            _checked = true;
            if (!string.Equals(relative, "register-owner", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
                Nav.NavigateTo("/register-owner", replace: true);
            return;
        }

        // 2) Not first run: only gate the site root
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(relative))
        {
            var auth = AuthenticationStateTask is null ? null : await AuthenticationStateTask;
            var isAuth = auth?.User?.Identity?.IsAuthenticated == true;
            _checked = true;
            Nav.NavigateTo(isAuth ? "/dashboard" : "/login", replace: true);
            return;
        }

        // 3) Any other route: no redirect
        _checked = true;
    }
}